HEADWORD: Quintole
<hw>Quin"tole</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It.
<ets>quinto</ets> fifth.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A group of five
notes to be played or sung in the time of four of the same
species.</def>⟦br⟧
